• Tell me about 5 different event types(event_type) in suricata.

- Alert: This is an event records for rule matches. It can be generated when suricata rule is triggered

- Netflow: This records metadata about a network connection in a unidirectional way.

- Http: This logs http requests and responses like urls, methods and status code. 

- DNS: The records are logged as one entry for the request, and one entry for the response. It helps identify domain lookups.
  
- JSON flags: Its used to control the JSON output by specifying several flags

• For the following, save a screen shot as well as the query:
– Make a query to show all ssh traffic.
`sudo more -f /var/log/suricata/eve.json | jq 'select(.event_type == "ssh")' `

![alt text](image-1.png)

– Make a query to show all TCP traffic not on port 80.
`sudo more -f /var/log/suricata/eve.json | jq 'select(.event_type == "flow" and .proto == "TCP" and .dest_port != 80)' `

![alt text](image.png)

– Make a query for all alerts in eve.json, not just the last alerts.

`sudo more -f /var/log/suricata/eve.json | jq 'select(.event_type == "alert")' `

